# SIM4Action Platform — Architecture & Conventions

## Project Identity
- **Name:** SIM4Action (Social-Environmental Interactive Mapping Platform for Action)
- **Purpose:** Interactive web platform for social-environmental systems mapping and causal analysis
- **Domain:** Generic — any socio-environmental system (e.g., fisheries, water resources, urban ecosystems, energy systems, public health, agriculture, climate adaptation)
- **Philosophy:** Domain-agnostic engine; system-specific knowledge lives entirely in configuration and Google Sheets data, never in platform code

## Architecture Overview
This is a **single-engine, config-driven** platform:
- One shared codebase in `platform/` serves ALL system maps
- Each system map is defined by a config folder under `systems/{id}/`
- Systems are loaded via URL parameter: `app.html?system={id}`
- The `systems/catalogue.json` is the master registry of all system maps

## Project Structure
```
Sim4Action-Platform/
├── platform/                     # Shared engine (DO NOT duplicate per system)
│   ├── index.html               # Landing page: catalogue browser, add/edit/delete
│   ├── app.html                 # Main app (generic, config-driven per system)
│   ├── server.py                # Python HTTP server + REST API
│   ├── diffusion.js             # JS token diffusion simulation (runs in browser)
│   ├── diffusion.py             # Python token diffusion (Streamlit/Pyodide legacy)
│   ├── browser_analysis.py      # NetworkX analysis (runs via Pyodide in browser)
│   ├── feedback_loops.py        # Feedback loop detection (runs via Pyodide)
│   ├── networkx_loader.py       # Graph construction from Google Sheets (Pyodide)
│   ├── drawing-layer.js         # SVG annotation drawing layer
│   ├── drawing-integration.js   # Drawing toolbar and controls integration
│   ├── drawing-controls.css     # Drawing toolbar styles
│   └── assets/
│       └── sim4action-logo.png
├── systems/
│   ├── catalogue.json           # Master catalogue (categories + systems list)
│   └── {system_id}/             # One folder per system
│       ├── config.json          # System config (spreadsheets, images, metadata)
│       ├── system-image.png     # Optional system image
│       └── thumbnail.png        # Optional thumbnail (fallback: system-image.png)
└── README.md
```

## Technology Stack
| Layer | Technology | Notes |
|-------|-----------|-------|
| Frontend | HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+) | Single-page, no build step |
| Visualization | D3.js v7 | Force-directed network graph |
| Charts | Chart.js | Supplementary charts |
| Graph (client) | Graphology | Client-side graph operations |
| Graph (analysis) | NetworkX via Pyodide | In-browser Python for centrality, loops, etc. |
| In-browser Python | Pyodide | Loads NetworkX, pandas, etc. in WebAssembly |
| Data source | Google Sheets API v4 | FACTORS and RELATIONSHIPS tabs |
| Server | Python 3 `http.server` | Custom handler for static files + REST API |
| Diffusion (JS) | Custom `diffusion.js` | Token-based causal diffusion simulation |
| Diffusion (Python) | Custom `diffusion.py` | Legacy Streamlit-based diffusion (matplotlib, plotly, streamlit) |

## Key Conventions

### Naming
- System IDs: lowercase, underscores, alphanumeric (e.g., `urban_water_cycle`, `coastal_ecosystem`)
- Factor IDs: `V1`, `V2`, `V3`, ... (letter V + number)
- Relationship IDs: `R1`, `R2`, `R3`, ... (letter R + number)
- Python files: snake_case
- JavaScript files: kebab-case (e.g., `drawing-layer.js`)
- CSS files: kebab-case (e.g., `drawing-controls.css`)

### No Build Step
The frontend has NO build tools (no webpack, no npm, no bundler). All JS/CSS is loaded directly via `<script>` and `<link>` tags or CDN. Keep it this way unless explicitly asked to introduce a build system.

### Server Startup
Always run from the project root:
```bash
python3 platform/server.py [--port PORT]
```
Default port: 8000. The server auto-detects the project root.

### URL Routing
The server maps URLs to filesystem paths:
- `/` → `platform/index.html`
- `/app.html?system={id}` → `platform/app.html`
- `/systems/*` → `systems/*`
- `/api/*` → REST API endpoints
- Platform JS/CSS files are served from `platform/`

### REST API Endpoints
| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| GET | `/api/catalogue` | Return `systems/catalogue.json` |
| GET | `/api/systems/:id/config` | Return `systems/:id/config.json` |
| POST | `/api/systems` | Create new system |
| PUT | `/api/systems/:id` | Update system metadata |
| PUT | `/api/catalogue` | Replace full catalogue |
| DELETE | `/api/systems/:id` | Remove system + directory |

### CORS
All API responses include `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`. The server handles OPTIONS preflight.

## Critical Rules for AI Development
1. **Never create system-specific code in `platform/`** — the engine is generic and config-driven
2. **Never hardcode system IDs, spreadsheet IDs, or API keys** in platform code
3. **Always update `systems/catalogue.json`** when adding/removing systems
4. **Preserve the no-build-step frontend** — no npm, webpack, or bundlers
5. **Test with `python3 platform/server.py`** from the project root
6. **Google Sheets must be shared publicly** (Anyone with link → Viewer)
7. **Python files in `platform/` serve dual purposes**: some run server-side (server.py), others run in-browser via Pyodide (networkx_loader.py, feedback_loops.py, browser_analysis.py)
